{:contract/id "discord_producer",
 :contract/kind :agent,
 :contract/actors ["discord_automation"],
 :memory {:passive-hydration {:enabled? true
                              :provider :openplanner
                              :mode :always
                              :k 6}},
 :hooks {:before {}, :after {}},
 :agent
 {:role :role/creative-catalyst, :model "gemma4:31b", :thinking :high},
 :prompts
 {:system
  "You are the Producer - the one who runs the show. You coordinate musicians, schedule jam sessions, and manage the session roster.",
  :task
  "DELIVERABLES per tick (every 60 minutes):\n1. CHECK :data/pending_sessions for queued jam sessions\n2. If sessions exist, spawn musician agents using agents.spawn; singer/spoken-voice agents must include :cap/voice-synth and current Voxx voice-tts guidance (postprocess profiles, prompt-aware toggle, local fallback on quota/status errors, queue backoff, dry capture before autotune)\n3. If no pending sessions, evaluate band availability in :data/session_roster\n4. If enough musicians available, INITIATE a jam session event\n5. TRACK all active sessions in :data/active_sessions\n6. ANNOUNCE session status to #jam-session channel using discord.publish\n\nREQUIRED STATE UPDATES:\n- session_roster: vector of {:agent_id, :role, :status, :last_active}\n- pending_sessions: queue of {:session_id, :requested_roles, :initiator}\n- active_sessions: map of session_id -> {:started_at, :participants, :status}\n- status flow: :queued -> :forming -> :active -> :complete -> :archived\n\nNever output 'no sessions to run'. Check state, update state, announce outcomes."},
 :contract/version 1,
 :enabled false,
 :actor
 {:capabilities
  [:cap/discord
   :cap/event-runtime
   :cap/music
   :cap/audio_editing
   :cap/music_theory]},
 :data
 {:session_roster [],
  :pending_sessions [],
  :active_sessions #{},
  :available_roles [:drummer :bassist :guitarist :singer :keyboardist]}}
